cs.SD, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SD. 

The paper deals with using Deep Neural Networks (DNNs) for speaker and language recognition tasks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SD (Sound). However, since the paper also involves using learned feature representations and sub-phoneme posteriors, it could also fall under cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, since DNNs are a type of artificial intelligence, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also a possible category. Finally, since the paper deals with performance improvements on specific tasks, it could also fall under cs.SD (Systems and Control).
